214
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:04,000
 Where do you stand?

215
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:07,000
 Ask yourself, do you love Jesus Christ?

216
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
 Or are you faking it?

217
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:14,000
 Judas faked it for three years, and Jesus still pursued him and loved him.

218
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:19,000
 I faked it for 13 years of my life.

219
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,000
 Like this was my story.

220
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:24,000
 I came to Christ, or I said the sinner's prayer at 8.

221
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 At the end of my mom's bed, it was nothing more than fire insurance, parents' divorce, never got plugged back into church,

222
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 and went off to college, and my life was a train wreck.

223
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,000
 I mean, not literally.

224
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:40,000
 I mean, people would say, oh, Josiah's got everything.

225
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,000
 Some of you have heard my story.

226
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:44,000
 I share it often.

227
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:50,000
 And I was playing college baseball and thinking that I had everything at my fingertips.

228
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 But it left me empty and unfulfilled.

229
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 And so I had a Bible because that's just what religious people do.

230
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 You usually have a Bible, and sometimes you might even go to church.

231
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,000
 I went to church at times.

232
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:06,000
 I wore that cross necklace around my neck, but my life looked no different than the rest of the world.

233
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:15,000
 I was hiding behind two-dimensional images, behind my computer, and sexual immorality with multiple women and partying.

234
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 You know it.

235
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:19,000
 You know that lifestyle, some of you.

236
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 And I remember opening the Bible to 2 Corinthians 13:5, and in 2 Corinthians 13:5, Paul is going to the church in Corinth,

237
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 and he just says, hey, I'm not going to affirm whether you're saved or not.

238
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
 That's not my job.

239
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:37,000
 I'm not going to say, hey, do you remember that time when you walked the aisle or you committed your life to, you know, church camp?

240
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,000
 He doesn't do any of that.

241
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:44,000
 He just says examine your life and test your faith against what the Word of God says and see if your faith is truly genuine.

242
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,000
 And I was like, whoa.

243
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:55,000
 When I started testing my life against this book, I was like, man, there's no way I'm saved.

244
00:19:55,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 I John 3 says when you live in continuous sin, it shows that you belong to the devil who has been sinning since the beginning.

245
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:08,000
 But the Son of God, Jesus, came to destroy the works of the devil, and those who have been born into God's family do not make a practice of sinning because God is in them.

246
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:11,000
 And listen, he's not saying that you're never going to sin.

247
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:16,000
 He says, you're not going to make a practice of sinning and never experience any life change.

248
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:25,000
 And I looked back on my life for 13 years, and there was little to no life change.

249
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:29,000
 And so, man, all I knew was like, man, I'm broken.

250
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,000
 My mouth has stopped of all justification.

251
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,000
 I need Jesus.

252
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,000
 And I knew what that word practice meant.

253
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:39,000
 I did it every day on the baseball field.

254
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,000
 Doing the same thing over and over and over and over until you master it.

255
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,000
 I was really good at sin.

256
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 Really good at sinning.

257
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:51,000
 And so I faked it.

258
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:56,000
 Do you believe in the Jesus who lives or the Jesus who lived?

259
00:20:56,000 --> 00:21:05,000
 The Jesus who lived 2,000 years ago, died on a cross and rose again on the third day to defeat sin and death, and now he's the poster child for Christianity, and now you subscribe to him.

260
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,000
 But your life has little to no bearing.

261
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:11,000
 Your life doesn't really reflect him.

262
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:15,000
 Or do you believe in the Jesus who lives?

263
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:26,000
 That Jesus died on the cross for your sins, rose again, sits at the right hand of the father, he rules and reigns over everything and even your life.

264
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:32,000
 And you give him allegiance to the broken areas of your life.

265
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:40,000
 Like when you in the Bible disagree who wins, it's one of my favorite questions to ask.

266
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:43,000
 Do you submit to the things of God?

267
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,000
 I'm not talking about perfection.

268
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,000
 No one's perfect.

269
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,000
 No, not one.

270
00:21:48,000 --> 00:22:02,000
 But I am talking about a desire, an oomph, a passion, a calling to be God's man, to be God's woman.

271
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:12,000
 Verse 6...

272
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:16,000
 Jesus answered, what I am doing, Peter, you're not going to understand now.

273
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:19,000
 But afterwards you will understand.

274
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:22,000
 Peter said to him, you shall never wash my feet.

275
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:29,000
 Peter was just like, no, no, Jesus, this is not what you -- you're like the king of kings.

276
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:32,000
 That's not what you do, Jesus.

277
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:38,000
 See, for some of you, Jesus comes to serve you but you're too proud to be served.

278
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:41,000
 And you think you're humble because you serve others.

279
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 Humility is not just serving, it's also being humble enough to let other people serve you and ultimately in this context let Jesus serve you.

280
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 How does Jesus serve you?

281
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:59,000
 Have you recognized that you're a sinner separated from him, you need saving?

282
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:02,000
 Have you recognized that?

283
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:05,000
 Have you seen your need for Jesus?

284
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:13,000
 So Jesus answered him, okay, Peter, if you don't want me to wash your feet, if I do not wash you, you have no share with me.

285
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:17,000
 Jesus is like, okay, I can wash your feet or you can go to hell.

286
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:20,000
 You know, like I just love like the bluntness of Jesus.

287
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:23,000
 You know, that's a paraphrased version, right.

288
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,000
 But that's just Jesus.

289
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:29,000
 Like plan A, Jesus I wash you and forgive you of your sin.

290
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,000
 Or plan B, it won't end well for you.

291
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,000
 Which one you want.

292
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:49,000
 Look at Peter's response...

293
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:56,000
 So here's Peter speaking up and says, Jesus, you're going to wash my feet.

294
00:23:56,000 --> 00:24:04,000
 Then Jesus makes a declaration which is an explanation to the simple gospel that unless I wash you then, you have no part with me.

295
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:08,000
 This foot washing is more than a physical act here.

296
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 It is a painting a spiritual picture of what Jesus has done for every single one of us.

297
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:16,000
 The simple gospel is explained here.

298
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 Just like Jesus is washing the disciples' feet, Jesus would shed his blood to wash our sin.

299
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:31,000
 The only way that we would come into a relationship with God is through the cross which washes away our sin.

300
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:36,000
 The only way that we can come into a relationship with the eternal God is when we say, God, I need you.

301
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:38,000
 God, I can't, but you can.

302
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:43,000
 There's nothing I can do to get to be made right with you.

303
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:53,000
 It's only through your death and your victory over the tomb when you rose from the dead snatching the keys to life and death.

304
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,000
 Like this is what he's saying.

305
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,000
 Like you can't wash yourself with good works.

306
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,000
 You can't wash yourself with religiosity.

307
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:06,000
 You can't wash yourself with, well, I hope my bad outweighs my good with charitable acts.

308
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:12,000
 Ephesians 2.8 and 9 says it clear, you have been saved by grace through faith not of yourself.

309
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,000
 It's a gift from God so no man may boast.

310
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:19,000
 If you could get to heaven based on what you do, what was the point of Jesus?

311
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,000
 Dying on the cross.

