00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,000
 And so we go to Texas Roadhouse.

326
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:57,000
 And we're talking to our waiter, D., and we're having a great conversation with him.

327
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,000
 He's a young adult and he's doing a great job.

328
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:02,000
 And so we're just getting to know him and what he's doing.

329
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:04,000
 And I just turned to D.

330
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,000
 And I just said, "D., I'm curious.

331
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,000
 Do you have a faith?"

332
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,000
 He said, "No, man, not really.

333
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:13,000
 I mean, I kind of heard a little bit about Jesus growing up.

334
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:16,000
 But then, you know, just kind of fell away."

335
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,000
 And I said, "Okay.

336
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,000
 No big deal."

337
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:20,000
 I said, "D., you believe that you're a sinner?

338
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:22,000
 You don't think you're perfect?"

339
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:24,000
 "No, man, I'm far from perfect.

340
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:26,000
 And I don't need to know everything.

341
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:28,000
 But I believe that too.

342
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,000
 I'm far from perfect.

343
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,000
 And this is what God's done in my life."

344
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:37,000
 And I just said, "D., if you don't allow God to wash you from your sin,

345
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:44,000
 then whose sin is -- then what are you going to do with your sin?"

346
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,000
 I said.

347
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:49,000
 Like who is your sin on, to be more specific?

348
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:51,000
 He pauses for a second.

349
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:52,000
 He thinks.

350
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:55,000
 And he says, "Me."

351
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:58,000
 And I said, "That's right."

352
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:01,000
 I said, "Does that concern you?"

353
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,000
 He said, "Yeah, it kind of actually does."

354
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:06,000
 I said, "Well, I'm preaching tomorrow at Sunday service.

355
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:08,000
 I'd love for you to come."

356
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,000
 No, I didn't -- I mean, I invited him.

357
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:13,000
 But we had a great conversation.

358
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,000
 And I was just talking to him.

359
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:18,000
 And I just said, "D., you can either ask God to wash you from your sin

360
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:20,000
 or your sin can stay on you.

361
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:23,000
 Either your sin is going to be on Jesus or it's going to be on you.

362
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:27,000
 Which one do you want your sin to be on?"

363
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:31,000
 And the same is true for everyone in this room.

364
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:34,000
 Your sin will either be on you or it will be on Jesus.

365
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:43,000
 Who are you trusting tonight to wash your sin?

366
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,000
 I love what A.W. Tozer says.

367
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:49,000
 He says, "The only sin Jesus ever had was ours.

368
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:53,000
 And the only righteousness we can ever have is his."

369
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,000
 Gosh.

370
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:57,000
 Let me just read that one more time.

371
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:00,000
 "The only sin Jesus ever had was ours."

372
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:02,000
 It means he's perfect, thought, word, and action.

373
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:06,000
 "And the only righteousness we can ever have is his."

374
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:12,000
 Where are you going to go to be made right with an eternal God?

375
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:16,000
 One commentary says, "The fact that this is in the Bible, John 13,

376
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:21,000
 Jesus stooping down to wash feet, says that this book was not written by man

377
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:24,000
 because men don't think this way."

378
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:31,000
 There's enough evidence just in this story that this book wasn't written by man.

379
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:36,000
 We don't think this way.

380
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:41,000
 Verse 12, "When he had washed their feet and put on his outer garments

381
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:45,000
 and resumed his place, he said to them,

382
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:47,000
 'Do you understand what I have done?

383
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:51,000
 You call me teacher and Lord, and you are right, for so I am.

384
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:55,000
 If then your Lord and teacher have washed your feet,

385
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:58,000
 you also shall wash one another's feet.

386
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:01,000
 For I have given you an example that also you should do

387
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,000
 as I have done to you.'"

388
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,000
 So as a response to this message,

389
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 we're going to give you an opportunity tonight to get your feet washed.

390
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:11,000
 And some of you are like, "What? I'm playing."

391
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,000
 Take a deep breath. Just kidding, okay?

392
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:17,000
 Some of you are so uncomfortable that you start looking for the exits.

393
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,000
 No, that's not what we're going to do.

394
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:21,000
 But think about it for a second.

395
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,000
 Like, this is crazy.

396
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:26,000
 Like, what if that was the response?

397
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:28,000
 You'd be like, "I'm out, bro.

398
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:34,000
 I'm heading to get food a lot earlier than I thought."

399
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:38,000
 But seriously, take some thought to this.

400
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,000
 Why would you even have that?

401
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,000
 Because it's uncomfortable.

402
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,000
 It's hard.

403
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:46,000
 It takes a great deal of humility because you recognize that you're needy.

404
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:49,000
 And I believe Jesus is giving us this language figuratively,

405
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:53,000
 not necessarily so that we wash each other's feet.

406
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:56,000
 But can you imagine the intensity of this scene

407
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:59,000
 as they're seeing their Lord, their teacher,

408
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:02,000
 the guy that they revere?

409
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:06,000
 He stoops down, gets on the floor, washes their feet,

410
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:10,000
 done what would only be expected by the most lowly servant in that house.

411
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:14,000
 And so he's having the last supper, his last meal with his boys.

412
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:21,000
 And in that culture, it was normalized to wash your feet before the meal.

413
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:23,000
 But no one had washed their feet.

414
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:25,000
 Why?

415
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:31,000
 Because nobody in that room, at that table,

416
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:35,000
 they didn't have the mindset,

417
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:39,000
 they didn't have the humility to say, "You know what?

418
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 I'll do that.

419
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,000
 I'm not above that.

420
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,000
 Where's the water?

421
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,000
 Where's the basin?

422
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:46,000
 Let's go.

423
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:47,000
 Where's the towel?"

424
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:48,000
 None of them did.

425
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:51,000
 And so they're sitting at a meal that most of the time in that culture,

426
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:53,000
 you would not eat until your feet were washed,

427
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:55,000
 and none of them had their feet washed

428
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 because every single one of the disciples said,

429
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,000
 "I'm not going that low.

430
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:07,000
 I'm not going to the lowest servant in the house.

431
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 I'm not doing that."

432
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:11,000
 And we all have that mentality, right,

433
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:16,000
 as we do life and our culture here in Dallas?

434
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:18,000
 Like, what's the threshold for you?

435
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:20,000
 I'm not going to do that.

436
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:21,000
 I'm above that.

437
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:25,000
 I'm beneath that.

438
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 What is it for you?

439
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:33,000
 And Jesus is trying to show us what greatness really is.

440
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:39,000
 He's trying to redefine greatness with a towel and a basin.

441
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 Think about one way that you could serve over the next 24 hours.

442
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 Think through how can I do what Jesus has done.

443
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:50,000
 And obviously it's not just a one-time thing.

444
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:51,000
 It's not just a 24-hour thing.

445
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:52,000
 It's a lifestyle.

446
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:55,000
 But to stoop and serve in a way that would be surprising

447
00:31:55,000 --> 00:32:01,000
 and even shocking to a culture of Dallas.

